From {{inh|en|enm|helle}}, from {{inh|en|ang|hel}}, {{m|ang|hell}}, {{m|ang|helle|t=nether world, abode of the dead, hell}}, from {{inh|en|gem-pro|*haljō|t=nether world, concealed place}}, from {{der|en|ine-pro|*ḱel-|t=to cover, conceal, save}}. Cognate with {{cog|stq|Hälle|t=hell}}, {{cog|fy|hel|t=hell}}, {{cog|nl|hel|t=hell}}, {{cog|nds-de|Hell|t=hell}}, {{cog|de|Hölle|t=hell}}, {{cog|sv|helvete|t=hell}}, {{cog|is|hel|t=the abode of the dead, death}}. Also related to the {{m|en|Hel}} of [[Germanic]] [[mythology]]. See also {{l|en|hele}}.

